description.narrative: WCARO contributed to accelerating the child health agenda in 20 countries through partnerships building and multisectoral collaboration for advocacy and better programming, evidence generation and review of national plans, partnerships development for resource mobilization, and capacity building initiatives for better implementation and knowledge generation to accelerate key results for children. WCARO strategically influenced the Primary Health Care (PHC) agenda by organizing a high-level regional forum which led to strong commitments from participative Ministers, a common agreement to establish a ministerial PHC dashboard for better accountability, and the Declaration of Cotonou which reinforces the urgency to increase investments for community-based PHC. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:17/01/2020
